The political class in the Democratic Republic of Congo is going through a new configuration. Since Félix Tshisekedi's call on October 23 for the "political forces" to unite in what the Congolese Head of State has described as the "sacred union of the nation", political actors are joining the camp that Tshisekedi intends to put in place. 



