When he took power in January 2019, the current Head of State had a double commitment. A commitment with his Chief of Staff and ally of Cape for Change (CACH), Vital Kamerhe, and another with the FCC and its leader, Joseph Kabila.
Now, Kamerhe is in prison for eight months while Kabila and his FCC find themselves in a difficult place.
However, some observers say that while the power games may sideline Kabila’s camp from central power in Kinshasa, other ambitious politicians are whetting their appetites ahead of the 2023 election. Kabila had succeeded in forming an army with many generals said to still be loyal to him. Nevers Mumba, of the Movement for Multiparty Democracy, says he has not been arrested. According to Kampala Archbishop, politicians are not following Covid rules. Her 12-year-old son survived after managing to swim to safety. The group said it had taken the chief prisoner during an attack on a Kenyan police outpost.